LMK_KEY.original_description: Individual lodgement identifier. Guaranteed to be unique and can be used to identify a certificate in the downloads and the API.

CURRENT_ENERGY_RATING.original_description: Current energy rating converted into a linear 'A to G' rating (where A is the most energy efficient and G is the least energy efficient)

POTENTIAL_ENERGY_RATING.original_description: Estimated potential energy rating converted into a linear 'A to G' rating (where A is the most energy efficient and G is the least energy efficient)

CURRENT_ENERGY_EFFICIENCY.original_description: Based on cost of energy, i.e. energy required for space heating, water heating and lighting [in kWh/year] multiplied by fuel costs. (/m/year where cost is derived from kWh).

POTENTIAL_ENERGY_EFFICIENCY.original_description: The potential energy efficiency rating of the property.

PROPERTY_TYPE.original_description: Describes the type of property such as House, Flat, Maisonette etc. This is the type differentiator for dwellings.

BUILT_FORM.original_description: The building type of the Property e.g. Detached, Semi-Detached, Terrace etc. Together with the Property Type, the Build Form produces a structured description of the property

INSPECTION_DATE.original_description: The date that the inspection was actually carried out by the energy assessor

LOCAL_AUTHORITY.original_description: Office for National Statistics (ONS) code. Local authority area in which the building is located.

CONSTITUENCY.original_description: Office for National Statistics (ONS) code. Parliamentary constituency in which the building is located.

COUNTY.original_description: County in which the building is located (where applicable)

LODGEMENT_DATE.original_description: Date lodged on the Energy Performance of Buildings Register

TRANSACTION_TYPE.original_description: Type of transaction that triggered EPC. For example, one of: marketed sale; non-marketed sale; new-dwelling; rental; not sale or rental; assessment for Green Deal; following Green Deal; FIT application; none of the above; RHI application; ECO assessment. Where the reason for the assessment is unknown by the energy assessor the transaction type will be recorded as 'none of the above'. Transaction types may be changed over time.

ENERGY_CONSUMPTION_CURRENT.original_description: Current estimated total energy consumption for the property in a 12 month period (kWh/m2). Displayed on EPC as the current primary energy use per square metre of floor area.

ENERGY_CONSUMPTION_POTENTIAL.original_description: Estimated potential total energy consumption for the Property in a 12 month period. Value is Kilowatt Hours per Square Metre (kWh/m)

CO2_EMISSIONS_CURRENT.original_description: CO emissions per year in tonnes/year.

CO2_EMISS_CURR_PER_FLOOR_AREA.original_description: CO emissions per square metre floor area per year in kg/m

CO2_EMISSIONS_POTENTIAL.original_description: Estimated value in Tonnes per Year of the total CO emissions produced by the Property in 12 month period.

LIGHTING_COST_CURRENT.original_description: GBP. Current estimated annual energy costs for lighting the property.

LIGHTING_COST_POTENTIAL.original_description: GBP. Potential estimated annual energy costs for lighting the property after improvements have been made.

HEATING_COST_CURRENT.original_description: GBP. Current estimated annual energy costs for heating the property.

HEATING_COST_POTENTIAL.original_description: GBP. Potential annual energy costs for lighting the property after improvements have been made.

HOT_WATER_COST_CURRENT.original_description: GBP. Current estimated annual energy costs for hot water

HOT_WATER_COST_POTENTIAL.original_description: GBP. Potential estimated annual energy costs for hot water after improvements have been made.

TOTAL_FLOOR_AREA.original_description: The total useful floor area is the total of all enclosed spaces measured to the internal face of the external walls, i.e. the gross floor area as measured in accordance with the guidance issued from time to time by the Royal Institute of Chartered Surveyors or by a body replacing that institution. (m)

ENERGY_TARIFF.original_description: Type of electricity tariff for the property, e.g. single.

MAINS_GAS_FLAG.original_description: Whether mains gas is available. Yes means that there is a gas meter or a gas-burning appliance in the dwelling. A closed-off gas pipe does not count.

FLOOR_LEVEL.original_description: Flats and maisonettes only. Floor level relative to the lowest level of the property (0 for ground floor). If there is a basement, the basement is level 0 and the other floors are from 1 upwards

FLAT_TOP_STOREY.original_description: Whether the flat is on the top storey

FLAT_STOREY_COUNT.original_description: The number of storeys in the apartment block.

MAIN_HEATING_CONTROLS.original_description: Type of main heating controls. Includes both main heating systems if there are two.

MULTI_GLAZE_PROPORTION.original_description: The estimated banded range (e.g. 0% - 10%) of the total glazed area of the Property that is multiple glazed.

GLAZED_TYPE.original_description: The type of glazing. From British Fenestration Rating Council or manufacturer declaration, one of; single; double; triple.

GLAZED_AREA.original_description: Ranged estimate of the total glazed area of the Habitable Area.

EXTENSION_COUNT.original_description: The number of extensions added to the property. Between 0 and 4.

NUMBER_HABITABLE_ROOMS.original_description: Habitable rooms include any living room, sitting room, dining room, bedroom, study and similar; and also a non-separated conservatory. A kitchen/diner having a discrete seating area (with space for a table and four chairs) also counts as a habitable room. A non-separated conservatory adds to the habitable room count if it has an internal quality door between it and the dwelling. Excluded from the room count are any room used solely as a kitchen, utility room, bathroom, cloakroom, en-suite accommodation and similar and any hallway, stairs or landing; and also any room not having a window.

NUMBER_HEATED_ROOMS.original_description: The number of heated rooms in the property if more than half of the habitable rooms are not heated.

LOW_ENERGY_LIGHTING.original_description: The percentage of low energy lighting present in the property as a percentage of the total fixed lights in the property. 0% indicates that no low-energy lighting is present.

NUMBER_OPEN_FIREPLACES.original_description: The number of Open Fireplaces in the Property. An Open Fireplace is a fireplace that still allows air to pass between the inside of the Property and the outside.

HOTWATER_DESCRIPTION.original_description: Overall description of the property feature

HOT_WATER_ENERGY_EFF.original_description: Energy efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

HOT_WATER_ENV_EFF.original_description: Environmental efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

FLOOR_DESCRIPTION.original_description: Overall description of the property feature

FLOOR_ENERGY_EFF.original_description: Energy efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

FLOOR_ENV_EFF.original_description: Environmental efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

WINDOWS_DESCRIPTION.original_description: Overall description of the property feature

WINDOWS_ENERGY_EFF.original_description: Energy efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

WINDOWS_ENV_EFF.original_description: Environmental efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

WALLS_DESCRIPTION.original_description: Overall description of the property feature

WALLS_ENERGY_EFF.original_description: Energy efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

WALLS_ENV_EFF.original_description: Environmental efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

SECONDHEAT_DESCRIPTION.original_description: Overall description of the property feature

SHEATING_ENERGY_EFF.original_description: Energy efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

SHEATING_ENV_EFF.original_description: Environmental efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

ROOF_DESCRIPTION.original_description: Overall description of the property feature

ROOF_ENERGY_EFF.original_description: Energy efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

ROOF_ENV_EFF.original_description: Environmental efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

MAINHEAT_DESCRIPTION.original_description: Overall description of the property feature

MAINHEAT_ENERGY_EFF.original_description: Energy efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

MAINHEAT_ENV_EFF.original_description: Environmental efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

MAINHEATCONT_DESCRIPTION.original_description: Overall description of the property feature

MAINHEATC_ENERGY_EFF.original_description: Energy efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

MAINHEATC_ENV_EFF.original_description: Environmental efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

LIGHTING_DESCRIPTION.original_description: Overall description of the property feature

LIGHTING_ENERGY_EFF.original_description: Energy efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

LIGHTING_ENV_EFF.original_description: Environmental efficiency rating. One of: very good; good; average; poor; very poor. On actual energy certificate shown as one to five star rating.

MAIN_FUEL.original_description: The type of fuel used to power the central heating e.g. Gas, Electricity

WIND_TURBINE_COUNT.original_description: Number of wind turbines; 0 if none.

HEAT_LOSS_CORRIDOR.original_description: Flats and maisonettes only. Indicates that the flat contains a corridor through which heat is lost. Heat loss corridor, one of: no corridor; heated corridor; unheated corridor

UNHEATED_CORRIDOR_LENGTH.original_description: The total length of unheated corridor in the flat. Only populated if flat or maisonette contains unheated corridor. If unheated corridor, length of sheltered wall (m).

FLOOR_HEIGHT.original_description: Average height of the storey in metres.

PHOTO_SUPPLY.original_description: Percentage of photovoltaic area as a percentage of total roof area. 0% indicates that a Photovoltaic Supply is not present in the property.

SOLAR_WATER_HEATING_FLAG.original_description: Indicates whether the heating in the Property is solar powered.

MECHANICAL_VENTILATION.original_description: Identifies the type of mechanical ventilation the property has. This is required for the RdSAP calculation.

ADDRESS.original_description: Field containing the concatenation of address1, address2 and address3. Note that post code is recorded separately.

LOCAL_AUTHORITY_LABEL.original_description: The name of the local authority area in which the building is located. This field is for additional information only and should not be relied upon: please refer to the Local Authority ONS Code.

CONSTITUENCY_LABEL.original_description: The name of the parliamentary constituency in which the building is located. This field is for additional information only and should not be relied upon: please refer to the Constituency ONS Code.

POSTTOWN.original_description: The post town of the property

LODGEMENT_DATETIME.original_description: Date and time lodged on the Energy Performance of Buildings Register.

TENURE.original_description: Describes the tenure type of the property. One of: Owner-occupied; Rented (social); Rented (private).

FIXED_LIGHTING_OUTLETS_COUNT.original_description: The number of fixed lighting outlets.

LOW_ENERGY_FIXED_LIGHT_COUNT.original_description: The number of low-energy fixed lighting outlets.

UPRN.original_description: The UPRN submitted by an assessor or alternatively from the departments address matching algorithm.

UPRN_SOURCE.original_description: Populated with the values "Energy Assessor" or "Address Matched" to show how the UPRN was populated.

REPORT_TYPE.original_description: Type of assessment carried out on the building, for domestic dwellings this is either a SAP (Standard Assessment Procedure) or a Reduced SAP. 100: RdSAP (Reduced SAP for existing buildings) and 101: SAP (full Sap for new dwellings, including conversions and change of use). This variable will help distinguish between new and existing dwellings.

LMK_KEY.original_description: Individual lodgement identifier. Guaranteed to be unique and can be used to identify a certificate in the downloads and the API.

ASSET_RATING.original_description: Energy Performance Asset Rating. The CO emissions from the actual building in comparison to a Standard Emission Rate. (kg CO/m)

ASSET_RATING_BAND.original_description: Energy Performance Asset Rating converted into an energy band/grade into a linear 'A+ to G' scale (where A+ is the most energy efficient and G the least energy efficient)

PROPERTY_TYPE.original_description: Describes the type of building that is being inspected. Based on planning use class.

INSPECTION_DATE.original_description: The date that the inspection was actually carried out by the energy assessor

LOCAL_AUTHORITY.original_description: Office for National Statistics (ONS) code. Local authority area in which the building is located.

CONSTITUENCY.original_description: Office for National Statistics (ONS) code. Parliamentary constituency in which the building is located.

COUNTY.original_description: County in which the building is located (where applicable)

LODGEMENT_DATE.original_description: Date lodged on the Energy Performance of Buildings Register

TRANSACTION_TYPE.original_description: Type of transaction that triggered EPC. One of: mandatory issue (marketed sale); mandatory issue (non-marketed sale); mandatory issue (property on construction); mandatory issue (property to let); voluntary re-issue (a valid epc is already lodged); voluntary (no legal requirement for an epc); not recorded. Transaction types may be changed over time.

EXISTING_STOCK_BENCHMARK.original_description: The Benchmark value of existing stock for this type of building

BUILDING_LEVEL.original_description: Building Complexity Level based on Energy Assessor National Occupation Standards

MAIN_HEATING_FUEL.original_description: Main Heating fuel for the building is taken as the fuel which delivers the greatest total thermal output for space or water heating

OTHER_FUEL_DESC.original_description: Text description of unspecified fuel type if 'Other' is selected for Main Heating Fuel

SPECIAL_ENERGY_USES.original_description: Special energy uses discounted. This only appears on the Recommendations Report.

RENEWABLE_SOURCES.original_description: On-site renewable energy sources. This only appears on the Advisory Report.

FLOOR_AREA.original_description: The total useful floor area is the total of all enclosed spaces measured to the internal face of the external walls, i.e. the gross floor area as measured in accordance with the guidance issued from time to time by the Royal Institute of Chartered Surveyors or by a body replacing that institution. (m2)

STANDARD_EMISSIONS.original_description: Standard Emission Rate is determined by applying a fixed improvement factor to the emissions from a reference building. (kg CO/m/year).

TARGET_EMISSIONS.original_description: Standard Emission Rate is determined by applying a fixed improvement factor to the emissions from a reference building. (kg CO/m/year).

BUILDING_EMISSIONS.original_description: Building Emissions Rate. Annual CO emissions from the building. Decimal (kg CO/m)

AIRCON_PRESENT.original_description: Air Conditioning System. Does the building have an air conditioning system?

AIRCON_KW_RATING.original_description: Air conditioning System. Rating in kW

ESTIMATED_AIRCON_KW_RATING.original_description: Air Conditioning System. If exact rating unknown, what is the estimated total effective output rating of the air conditioning system

AC_INSPECTION_COMMISSIONED.original_description: One of:1=Yes, inspection completed; 2=Yes, inspection commissioned; 3=No inspection completed or commissioned; 4=Not relevant; 5=Don't know

BUILDING_ENVIRONMENT.original_description: Building environment which is taken as the servicing strategy that contributes the largest proportion of the building's CO emissions.

ADDRESS.original_description: Field containing the concatenation of address1, address2 and address3. Note that post code is recorded separately.

LOCAL_AUTHORITY_LABEL.original_description: The name of the local authority area in which the building is located. This field is for additional information only and should not be relied upon: please refer to the Local Authority ONS Code.

CONSTITUENCY_LABEL.original_description: The name of the parliamentary constituency in which the building is located. This field is for additional information only and should not be relied upon: please refer to the Constituency ONS Code.

POSTTOWN.original_description: The post town of the property

LODGEMENT_DATETIME.original_description: Date and time lodged on the Energy Performance of Buildings Register.

PRIMARY_ENERGY_VALUE.original_description: Displayed on the non-domestic EPC as primary energy use (kWh/m2 per year)

UPRN.original_description: The UPRN submitted by an assessor or alternatively from the departments address matching algorithm.

UPRN_SOURCE.original_description: Populated with the values "Energy Assessor" or "Address Matched" to show how the UPRN was populated.

REPORT_TYPE.original_description: Type of assessment carried out of the building. 102: assessment using the SBEM (Simplified Building Energy Model) tool for non-domestic (non-residential) buildings.
